This paper is about training deeper neural machine translation models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a modification to the attention mechanism, which is a key component of NMT models, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimizing the models, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions convolutional models used for text and vision applications, which could suggest a connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision).
